@node inventscorner "Ivents Corner"
@toc contents
============================================================================
          	 @{b}September 2023 Ivents Corner@{ub} 
============================================================================
I'm sure you're all enjoying the wonderful WhatIFF magazine as much as I 
am, my sincere apologies for not contributing to the last issue, a family 
health matter - my dear Wife had been extremely sick with a very rare 
disease, and a long recovery journey ahead, anyway back on to these fun 
Amiga projects.

Here are a few updates.

@{b}Amiga Art Contest 2023@{ub}

The Amiga Art Contest for 2023 is officially open, Doug/10Marc recently 
posted his official video announcing the start of this very exciting 
competition.  We have the same categories which are Hand Drawn, 
Photographs, 3D/Ray Traced, Animations, Music/MODS, Deadline is 11th 
November 2023. Please remember you can use Real or Emulated Amigas and 
Doug/myself are the two judges, Anyone who is a patreon of either of us can 
also vote for best in each category. We plan to have a few prizes, for the 
moment keeping some of them secret. As long as you have created the 
Art/Music using Amiga software your entry is valid. What we do also love is 
the description, process and inspiration story behind your creative efforts. 

Best of luck :)

@{b}Boss Machine@{ub}

Boss Machine I have been focusing on a lot more Big Bosses with detailed 
animation frames and ideas for how each of them move. I have posted lots of 
free content on my Patreon and various social sites, e.g. EAB forum :) 
Recently we did a test for some of those fast parallax scrollers to add more 
detail in the background, we can swap out some of the parallax splits with 
other unique graphic tiles. Another focus for me is the end level design. 
Technically the pixel height we have for some levels is 480 pixels and we 
have a few tricks up our sleeve to enhance end level areas such as adding 
caves to fly into, modifying colour palettes for the foreground/enemies that 
help blend into the background, I plan to post some of these ideas on my 
Patreon very soon.  Dan and I need to test this out first so expect a quick 
video or two :) 

In general Boss Machine is getting a lot more attention.

@{b}Apollo Invaders@{ub}

Space Invaders for all Apollo Vampires is constantly improving and right now 
we are focusing on adding more mid bosses (ten) as well as a reward system 
for every zone you complete. The game has 100 levels and everytime you 
complete a zone you get a medal for your achievements. Alongside these Mid 
level Bosses will have tiny children enemies that are simplified versions 
of the mothership. 

We plan to showcase this new update at Gamescon :) 

We do also plan to release a boxed version of the game, so this is also 
exciting news for anyone who loves to collect physical media. Sneak peek of 
these enemy designs on my Patreon blog :) 

Till next time,

Amiga Forever
Kev | Invent

@endnode

@node coverdisk "Cover Disk Number 3"
@toc contents
============================================================================
          	 @{b}September 2023 Cover Disk Contents@{ub} 
============================================================================

Welcome to our 3rd cover disk or rather 3rd contents folder, for this issue
we have playable demo of the in development BitBeam Cannon game 
Aeons Legend, here are few words from the developer about the demo:

@{i}Aeon Legends is currently being developed by the BitBeamCannon team using 
scorpion engine. Please be aware the game is still in early development WIP
and that the game is designed for at least 2 button controllers. 1 button 
is jump, one attack, hold up and attack to throw the projectile weapon, and 
top left shoulder button on CD32 (or space-bar) to switch the weapon you 
will throw between a boomerang or a bomb also, the little statues with e 
up-arrows are like guidesigns.. if you walk onto them and tap up text will 
appear with clues for the things you can do in the game.

This is not a real level designed to be fun, it's a demo level to show the 
progress and game features.@{ui}

In addition we have multi-module for your listening pleasure, and here are
words from one of the artists involved:

@{i}Acidic breakcore OctaMED multi-module by Mr. Roboto, df0:BAD & cTrix in 
2023. Over twenty minutes of music in about 1.2 uncompressed megabytes of 
data. For best results please use the latest version of Hippo Player if not 
OctaMED itself. Look out for the upcoming physical floppy music disk 
release in late november!@{ui}
 
